				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/echofourdelta" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(515520); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=515520&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610227442" alt="EchoFourDelta" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=515520)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/echofourdelta" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(515520); return false;" >EchoFourDelta</a></span> <span class="odate time_1384990805 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">20 Nov 2013 23:40</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1897565">
									

<p>If you're an author looking toward adding something here, take a few minutes and consider what you're writing, and what you're saying with your post.</p>
<p>It might seem cool to want to create some awesome combination of traits into some super agent that you hope someone might use, or to just dial up the badass. But think about it. That's not what this is about. The SCP's not about creating superheroes, or awesome-ass Foundation operatives, or anything like that.</p>
<p>Read the article, and consider what it does. Some of the things seem almost random, and not all are in any way positive. Upon close inspection, many of the changes made are illogical and damn near inscrutable. Keep that in mind as you write.</p>

							</div>

